The paper discusses the sample and Rademacher complexity bounds for manifold regularization, which is a commonly used technique in semi-supervised learning. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and can also be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), social and information networks (cs.SI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) as these fields often use semi-supervised learning techniques.
